### Linking a SCIM group to site admin (two-apply workflow)

The `site_admin_group_scim_id` argument links a SCIM group to the site admin role. The group must already exist in Terraform Enterprise, but groups are only created by your IdP after SCIM provisioning is enabled. This requires a two-apply workflow:

**Apply 1 — enable SCIM** so your IdP can begin pushing groups. Do **not** set `site_admin_group_scim_id` yet:

{{tffile "examples/resources/scim_settings/example_3.tf"}}

Run `terraform apply`, then wait for your IdP to provision the desired group into Terraform Enterprise via SCIM. Locate the SCIM ID of that group (for example, from the IdP's SCIM logs or by querying `GET /scim/v2/Groups`).

**Apply 2 — link the site admin group** by adding `site_admin_group_scim_id` to the same resource:

{{tffile "examples/resources/scim_settings/example_4.tf"}}

Keep `site_admin_group_scim_id` in your config from this point on. Removing it (or setting it to `""`) unlinks the group on the next apply.

## Argument Reference

The following arguments are supported:

* `paused` - (Optional) Whether SCIM provisioning is paused. Defaults to `false`.
* `site_admin_group_scim_id` - (Optional) The SCIM ID of the group to map to site admin. Defaults to `""` (unlinked).

`paused` and `site_admin_group_scim_id` are the only mutable arguments. To fully disable SCIM you must run `terraform destroy` on this resource; there is no argument to disable it in-place.

## Attributes Reference

* `id` - The ID of the SCIM Settings. Always `scim`.
* `enabled` - Whether SCIM provisioning is enabled. Always `true` while this resource exists; use `terraform destroy` to disable.
* `site_admin_group_display_name` - The display name of the SCIM group mapped to site admin. Empty when no group is linked.

## Import

SCIM Settings can be imported using the fixed ID `scim`.

```shell
terraform import tfe_scim_settings.this scim
```
